<br>
What is your camera position? (ie. first person, angled from above, distance, etc)<br>
<br>
What are your standard rules? (ie. against such-and-such, pumice this-and-which, keep such-and-such buffslot open by doing that-and-this)<br>
<br>
What are your primary goals? (ie. sticking on the person, wasting melee rounds, backstabbing or just meleeing)<br>
<br>
What tools do you use? (ie. jboots, mojo sticks, pumices, weapons, MR gear, etc etc)<br>
<br>
<br>
I've been dueling a little recently, in particular several times with shadowknight, once with a druid, and twice with a shaman...<br>
<br>
And I keep getting OWNED.  If I'm not getting kited around, I'm running around trying to actually hit the guy because I keep losing him and then getting jousted for massive damage while only backstabbing (if lucky) for maybe 40 dmg if I'm lucky-- usually I'm out of range or missing or just ending up piercing (and missing THAT too!).<br>
<br>
I'm a 40 rogue and I kept losing to that 39 SK, and he was giving himself lots of handicaps (ie. half health, not using certain spells, etc...)-- and he ended up with more health than he started at some times!  The druid was a friend of mine and he was 35!!  And he kited me to death!  Same with that 40 troll shaman.<br>
<br>
What am I doing wrong?  And how the heck do I stay on my target?  He keeps maneuvering and I take too much time trying to find him again.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvenomss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Venomss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/30/01 12:52:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP style</span><hr size=1> Get two or 3 golem wands.  2 for actual use, 1 for using to recharge the other 2 (i.e. sell one with charges, sell other drained ones, buy back all 3 with full charges)<br>
<br>
This insta-cast dispel will have all his buffs gone, and him in a hurt locker, particulary if you blind poison him/root poison him.  <br>
<br>
Once he has those buffs gone, you should be able to employ hide, as I think the number of folks on Blue servers lack a choker of majdd or bracer of hidden.<br>
<br>
-Venoms <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukgold0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kgold0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/30/01 10:19:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP style</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the advice.  I am on RZ though so many people will have the Majdd necklace.  How much does it cost to buy back one of those golem wands by the way?<br>
<br>
Thanks a lot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaejz69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaejz69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/4/01 12:26:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP style</span><hr size=1>   Mind you this is coming from a warrior <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 Style- All of em depending on the class I'm fighting<br>
 Camera- First person<br>
 Rules- All melee get hit with tash from my Jmans followed by jousting with a Truncheon of Doom. If I happened to have farmed any Wooly Silk Nets from perma, they get root too and I continue jousting.<br>
 Goals- Land slow as soon as possible, keep rogue posion off of me using a Dranon's Ring from Skyshrine (5 charges of instacast counteract poison), keep see invisible on with a bracer of the hidden<br>
 Tools- Jmans, ToD, Wooly Silk Nets, Dranons Ring, Bracer of the Hidden, Jboots, Sow Pots, Silken Whip of Ensnaring, jagged shard of bone (dropped in lfay for a while, fear proc)<br>
<br>
 As for you, when fighting an sk, just worry about him landing dot/snare on you and fear (so basically magic resist). Circle Strafe around him if possible. If he's jousting just try to keep behind him as he's moving and land a backstab or three. I'd suggest a see invis item as well, you don't want him running off and medding up while you look for him.<br>
<br>
 Druid dump a whole pumice stone on him if possible to get rid of sow and that nasty damage shield. Here, magic resist and fire resist are the keys. Drones of doom or whatnot is hard to resist anyways. A smart druid will invis when low on health/mana, so a see invis item is nice here too. <br>
<br>
 Start off a shaman the same as a druid, dump a pumice. Start with magic resist gear on a shaman; get slowed and you're done. They're cold nukes are pretty inefficient for mana, so they'll probably go with a poison or disease dot. I'd suggest a poison/disease resist of at least 40-50 here. See invis item applies here.<br>
<br>
  Finally, as a dueling rogue work your poison skill as much as you can. Against an unprepared opponent, landing a root/slow poison will almost ensure you a victory if you keep on em. <br>
<br>
  Against one of my buds (56 rogue with RB), I basically turn him into a ranger without spells by using my cure poison ring, bracer of the hidden, and jousting tactics. Unless I screw up somehow, I can beat him almost every time with my 57 warrior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaulonweck.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saulon Weck</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/01 10:53:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP style</span><hr size=1> where do you get the golem wands from?  i went on everlore, one person said befallen, another said cazic thule.  When you recharge, how much do they cost to buy back?  Can't believe i dont' know this yet >_<  I've always used pumice.<br>
